   <refnamediv>
       <refname>repmat</refname>
               <refpurpose>mimics Matlab function repmat </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[B]=repmat(A,m,n)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> A </term> =    a matrix</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> m </term> =    a scalar or a (1xk) vector</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> n </term> =    a scalar (used only if m is a scalar)</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> B </term> =    the replication and tiling of A</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Function that mimics Matlab function repmat, that replicates and tiles an array 

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
A = [1 2 3 ; 4 5 6];B=repmat(A,2,3)// returns
// B  =//!   1.    2.    3.    1.    2.    3.    1.    2.    3. !//!   4.    5.    6.    4.    5.    6.    4.    5.    6. !//!   1.    2.    3.    1.    2.    3.    1.    2.    3. !//!   4.    5.    6.    4.    5.    6.    4.    5.    6. ! 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
